🌐 DNS_App

-> A small distributed systems demo built in Python and Docker.

🚀 Features

-> Three independent microservices, each in its own Docker container
-> Custom DNS-style protocol built on raw UDP sockets
-> Service registration — a server announces itself to a directory service on startup
-> Name-based service lookup instead of hardcoded IPs
-> REST API (Flask) for computing Fibonacci numbers
-> Fully containerized with Docker Compose — one command to run everything

🛠️ Tech Stack

-> Python 3.9
-> Flask (REST APIs)
-> Raw UDP sockets (custom DNS-style protocol)
-> Docker & Docker Compose
-> Requests (inter-service HTTP calls)

📦 Project Structure

dns-fib-app/
├── docker-compose.yml
├── README.md
├── as/
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── authoritative_server.py
├── fs/
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── fibonacci_server.py
└── us/
    ├── Dockerfile
    └── user_server.py


✅ Prerequisites

-> [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/) installed and running
-> No authentication or input validation beyond basic checks — this is a learning/demo project, not a production service mesh
